@startuml fig-A05-message-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Port Scanner — E2 PCAP Flow (Open, Closed and Filtered Ports)

participant "h1\n(scanner)" as SC #FFE0B2
participant "s1" as SW #BBDEFB
participant "h2\n(victim)" as VIC #C8E6C9
participant "tcpdump" as CAP #ECEFF1

== OPEN PORT (port 80 — HTTP) ==

SC -[#43A047]> SW : SYN → :80
SW -> VIC : SYN
VIC -[#43A047]-> SW : SYN-ACK
SW -[#43A047]-> SC : SYN-ACK
SC -[#43A047]> SW : ACK (handshake complete)
note right of CAP : R2: SYN-ACK >= 1

SC -> SW : HTTP GET / (fingerprint probe)
VIC --> SC : HTTP 200 Server: nginx
note right of CAP #E8F5E9 : R4: frame contains\n"HTTP" or "Server:" >= 1
SC -> SW : FIN

== CLOSED PORT (port 22 — no service) ==

SC -[#E53935]> SW : SYN → :22
SW -> VIC : SYN
VIC -[#E53935]-> SW : RST
SW -[#E53935]-> SC : RST
note right of CAP : R3: RST >= 1\nclassification: closed

== FILTERED PORT (port 443 — drop rule) ==

SC -[#FF9800]> SW : SYN → :443
SW -> VIC : SYN (dropped by rule)
...
SC -[#FF9800]> SW : SYN retransmission → :443
...
SC -> SC : timeout reached\nclassification: filtered
note right of CAP : no SYN-ACK, no RST

== EVIDENCE ==

note right of CAP : R1: SYN (ack==0) >= 20
SC -> CAP : scan_report.json\n+ summary.md

legend right
  Three port states demonstrated in PCAP:
  open (SYN-ACK + banner), closed (RST)
  and filtered (timeout with retransmissions).
  Rate limiting keeps probes at max 200/s.
endlegend
@enduml
